{"lemma":"هُدْهُدَيْ","slug":"هُدْهُدَيْ","root":"ه.د.ه.د","root_slug":"ه-د-ه-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ه-د-ه-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"هُدْهُد","root":"هدهد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n40965","n40969","n40970"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%87%D9%8F%D8%AF%D9%92%D9%87%D9%8F%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to emit a modulated voice","tags":["ambitransitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"hoopoe","examples":[{"text":"وَتَفَقَّدَ ٱلطَّيْرَ فَقَالَ مَا لِيَ لَا أَرَى ٱلْهُدْهُدَ أَمْ كَانَ مِنَ ٱلْغَائِبِينَ","english":"˹One day˺ he inspected the birds, and wondered, “Why is it that I cannot see the hoopoe? Or could he be absent?"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Onomatopoeic reduplicated. Compare Classical Syriac ܝܕܝܕܐ (yaḏyāḏā, “hoopoe”).\n\nهُدْهُد"},"ipa":["/had.ha.da/","/hud.hud/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n40965","headword_ar":"هَدْهَدَ","root":"hd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hdohadapN","text_ar":"هدْهَدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a bird)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cooed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaroqara","text_ar":"قَرْقَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L, K, TA [in the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farofara","text_ar":"فَرْفَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a pigeon)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cooed"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hadara","text_ar":"هَدَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hadala","text_ar":"هَدَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made a murmuring"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"confused noise"},{"kind":"text","text":"in cooing: (S, L, accord to the explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hadohadapN","text_ar":"هَدْهَدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a camel, S, L)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brayed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hadara","text_ar":"هَدَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made a murmuring"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"confused noise"},{"kind":"text","text":"in braying (S, L,) See also 1. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hadohadato","text_ar":"هَدْهَدَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hadohadpN","text_ar":"هَدْهَدةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", L.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a woman, S, L)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shook,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rocked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a child (S, L, K) in its cradle, (L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in order that it might sleep."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hadohada","text_ar":"هَدْهَدَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"threw,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"down,"},{"kind":"text","text":"from a high place to a low one, (L, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","L","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n40969","headword_ar":"هَدْهَدٌ","root":"hd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"voices,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cries, of jinn,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"genii:"},{"kind":"text","text":"without a singular. (L, K)"}],"source_refs":["L","K"]},{"entry_id":"n40970","headword_ar":"هُدْهُدٌ","root":"hd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain bird,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, Msb, K;) [namely, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hoopee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upupa"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Linnæus; so this bird is called in the present day; and this, accord. to a common tradition, is the bird mentioned in the Kur, xxvii. 20;] as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hudahidN","text_ar":"هُدَهِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hudaAhidN","text_ar":"هُدَاهِدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, L, K:) or the last,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain bird resembling the pigeon:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, Az, L:) or (in the K, and)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hudohudN","text_ar":"هُدْهُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a pigeon that cooes much;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd in explanation"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2883},{"kind":"text","text":"of v. 20 of ch. xxvii. of the Kur., and AHn, L K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hudaAhidN","text_ar":"هُدَاهِدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IDrd, AHn, L:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any bird that cooes; that utters the cry called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaroqarap","text_ar":"قَرْقَرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (L, K, TA [in the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yufarofiru","text_ar":"يُفَرْفِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuqaroqiru","text_ar":"يُقَرْقِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hudaAhidN","text_ar":"هُدَاهِدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (As, L:) pl. (of all, K)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hadaAhidu","text_ar":"هَدَاهِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hadaAhiydu","text_ar":"هَدَاهِيدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Kr, L, K:) but ISd says of the latter, I know not how this is, unless the sing. be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hadohaAdN","text_ar":"هَدْهَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.) Er-Rá'ee says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"kahudaAhidK kasara Alr~umaApu janaAHahu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Like a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hdAhd","text_ar":"هداهد"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose wing the shooters have broken"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, L:) As says, he means the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAxitap","text_ar":"فَاخِتَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dubosiY~","text_ar":"دُبْسِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wara$aAn","text_ar":"وَرَشَان"},{"kind":"text","text":", or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hudohud","text_ar":"هُدْهُد"},{"kind":"text","text":", or a man, or camels: and Lh says, that Ks asserts him to mean, by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hdAhd","text_ar":"هداهد"},{"kind":"text","text":", the dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hudohudN","text_ar":"هُدْهُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but As disapproves of this; and so does ISd; but the latter adds, that it may perhaps be for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hudayohidN","text_ar":"هُدَيْهِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as some of the Arabs say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwaAb~apN","text_ar":"دُوَابَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uwaAb~apN","text_ar":"شُوَابَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwyob~apN","text_ar":"دُويْبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uwayob~apN","text_ar":"شُوَيْبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; though they are only known to change the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"before a double consonant. (L.)"}],"source_refs":["S","L","Msb","K","Lth","Az","IDrd","AHn","As","Kr"]}]}}